<!--
The in-loop readback message format. NOT committed to needs.md — used in the live conversation
between the model and the stakeholder. Replace each <slot> with the actual content for the turn.
-->

**Readback — <topic>**

What I heard you say:
> <paraphrase in stakeholder voice>

What I'm proposing to write:
> <candidate Needs entry, stakeholder-voice, prefixed with the section it would land in (e.g. "Quality needs: ...", "Constraint: ...", "Interfaces / integrations: ...")>

Is this right? Please reply with one of:
- **yes** — I'll commit as-is.
- **no — change X** — tell me what to change and I'll re-readback.
- **almost — also Y** — tell me what to add or adjust and I'll re-readback.

(Ambiguous replies like "ok" or "sure" — I'll treat as a request to keep elicitating, not a confirmation.)
